Pupworld Policies

Cancellation Policy

Buyer agrees that the Cancellation Fee is a fair and equitable amount for damages sustained by the Breeder and Company as the exact amount of damages is unknown and impossible to predict as time is of the essence because a Puppy’s value diminishes with time and even its ability to find a forever home diminishes with time. This is a time sensitive reservation and thus not a promise nor guarantee to the receipt of merchandise or fitness shall the Buyer not abide by its contractual obligations. This Agreement will remain in full force and effect if Buyer fails to fulfill its contractual obligations in a timely manner, including but not limited too, paying all invoices on time, remaining in constant communication, failure to be present at time of delivery, failure to accept delivery or take possession, all for which the Buyer will not be warranted a refund due to non-receipt of merchandise or fitness.

From the effective date of this Agreement (“Reservation Date”) up until 72 hours thereafter, Buyer may cancel the Reservation and receive a refund for the full Reservation Value less the Cancellation Fee of $499 plus fees and applicable taxes.

More than 72 hours after the Reservation Date, but before 72 hours of the Puppy’s Travel Date, Buyer shall receive a refund of 50% of the total Reservation Value less a Cancellation Fee of 50% of the total Reservation Value, not to be less than $499, excluding any Travel Costs.

Within 72 hours of the Puppy’s Travel Date, Buyer acknowledges and agrees that the reservation / sale is final, a Cancellation Fee of 100% of the Reservation Value will apply and that no refunds will be permitted.

If Buyer refuses the Puppy at any time after the designated Travel Date, during transit, or at the time of Delivery, Refusal of Delivery provisions will be in full force and effect. Buyer agrees Refusal of Delivery will result in a Cancellation Fee of 100% of the Reservation Value plus a $599 Return Transport Fee.

IMPORTANT (PLEASE READ): IF YOU DECIDE TO CANCEL THIS AGREEMENT UNDER THE TERMS SET FORTH ABOVE, YOU MUST (1) INITIATE CANCELLATION BY (a) CALLING 260-710-9103 OR (b) SENDING AN EMAIL TO 01PUPWORLD@GMAIL.COM OR (c) SENDING A MESSAGE VIA THE MESSAGE CENTER AND (2) CONFIRM CANCELLATION BY ELECTRONICALLY SIGNING THE“CONSENT TO CANCEL” AGREEMENT WITHIN 24 HOURS. FAILURE TO CONFIRM AN INITIATED CANCELLATION WILL BE FOUND IN DEFAULT, IDENTIFIED IN SECTION 31, AS TIME IS OF THE ESSENCE.IF BUYER DOES NOT FULFILL CANCELLATION PROTOCOLS ABOVE, OR DISPUTES A CHARGE, THEN BUYER SHALL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR ALL ASSOCIATED FEES AS IF THE AGREEMENT HAS NOT BEEN PROPERLY CANCELED.

Cancellation Notice Protocol

Refusal of Delivery: If Buyer refuses to accept delivery or delays in doing so or is not present at the time of Delivery (“Refusal”), (a) Delivery will be deemed to have occurred, and the Reservation deemed consummated for the purpose of this Agreement; (b) Buyer understands there are no refunds; Buyer will be subject to a return transport fee of $599.00 plus applicable taxes and Fees due immediately upon receipt including interest at a rate of a 1.5% compounded per twenty-one (21) calendar days computed from the date of Refusal.; (c) Pupworld shall retain the payments made to date by Buyer as liquidated damages; (d) Buyer agrees that Refusal will be considered, if necessary in part, as a Cancellation Notice and thus a Cancellation Fee of 100% the Reservation Value will apply with the Cancellation Date defined as the date of Refusal or Delivery; (e) Buyer understands and agrees it is considered inhumane, cruel and unfair to refuse the Puppy upon Delivery and that in doing so may subject the Puppy to added Veterinary fees, significant health risks, illness or even death due to prolonged transport resulting in monetary damages to the Breeder. Buyer agrees to be liable for any consequential damages. (f) The Parties shall have no further obligations to each other, except those which expressly survive the termination of this Agreement.

Refund Policy

PUPWORLD FEES ARE NON-REFUNDABLE. NO EXCEPTIONS.

BUYER UNDERSTANDS AND ACCEPTS THAT ALL RESERVATION PAYMENTS ARE FINAL AND NON-REFUNDABLE AS TIME IS OF THE ESSENCE WITH THE EXCEPTION OF THE FOLLOWING:

(1) A PARTIAL REFUND* OF THE RESERVATION VALUE MAY APPLY AS IT RELATES TO THE SCHEDULE OF CANCELLATION FEES IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE CANCELLATION POLICY.

IF BUYER CHOOSES NOT TO ACCEPT PUPPY UPON ARRIVAL OR DECLINES PUPPY DURING TRANSIT, BUYER UNDERSTANDS THERE ARE NO REFUNDS AND THE PROVISIONS WITHIN SECTION 13. REFUSAL OF DELIVERY WILL BE IN FULL FORCE AND EFFECT; BUYER AGREES TO NOTIFY PUPWORLD IMMEDIATELY AT 260-710-9103.

NO REFUNDS WITHIN 72 HOURS OF THE TRAVEL DATE. ALL PETS ARE SOLD AS-IS PER SECTION 10. PETS ARE SOLD AS-IS; NO WARRANTIES AND THUS BUYER WILL NOT RECEIVE A REFUND FOR ANY REASON WITHIN 72 HOURS OF THE TRAVEL DATE INCLUDING ANYTIME THEREAFTER INCLUDING POST DELIVERY.

*HEALTH GUARANTEE CLAIMS OFFER A FORM OF REIMBURSEMENT ONLY AND ARE NOT A REFUND FOR THE RESERVATION VALUE OF THE PUPPY.

*Refunds typically take 5-10 business days to appear on Your bank statement.

Chargebacks

If You file a dispute with Your bank or credit card company to decline a charge, request a chargeback, or otherwise reverse the amount of any payment made to Pupworld for the reservation of a Puppy, we reserve our right to dispute any chargebacks and provide documentation of this Agreement to defend Pupworld. If You file a chargeback without justification or excellent cause, You could face accidental fraud or theft charges. The Company’s right to file a civil lawsuit includes but is not limited to the assertion of causes of action of fraud, conversion, and/or breach of contract. Requesting an intentionally false chargeback is considered a deliberate scam to defraud a merchant and theft by deceit; You could face penalties and jail time. We urge You to please get in touch with us by email at 01pupworld@gmail.com or call 260-710-9103 before filing a dispute or chargeback.

Return Policy

PUPPY MUST BE RETURNED IF BUYER CANNOT CARE FOR IT.

Puppies typically need time to adjust to their new home and surroundings. Before deciding Your Puppy isn’t working out, please reach out to Pupworld for assistance in figuring out if any discomfort You or Your Puppy are having is due to routine adjustment or something else.

In any case, the company will not accept any returns of the Puppy for a monetary refund for any reason whatsoever. No refund or credit will be given to Buyer if the Puppy must be returned for any reason. Buyer will be responsible for all return travel expenses.

In the event Buyer is unable or unwilling to care for the pet at any time during the life of the pet, Buyer agrees to contact Pupworld immediately regarding rehoming the pet under a surrender basis only. If Buyer must return the Puppy for any reason, it will do so on a surrender basis only without any recourse for a refund or credit, and Buyer will be solely responsible for all travel-related costs. Upon any such surrender, the Breeder shall use commercially reasonable efforts to find a new home for the pet.

Information Collected or Received

PupWorld, LLC will not sell or disclose your name, email address or other personal

information to third parties without your explicit consent, except as specified in this policy. As a PupWorld, LLC member you are required to provide a valid email address at registration.

Depending on which services you choose to use, PupWorld, LLC may require additional information, such as your name, kennel name, billing and payment information (including billing address, telephone number, credit card information), a telephone number, and/or a physical postal address. PupWorld, LLC may require information such as your social security number or tax ID, date of birth, bank account information, credit card information and/or other proof of identification in order to verify your identity and provide this service to you. Credit card information on an account may be stored and used for both billing and payment purposes.

PupWorld, LLC may contact members to confidentially request more information about themselves or their kennel or pets listed on the site, to ensure compliance with our rules.

Your birthdate, gender, ethnicity will not be publicly displayed in connection to your

account and activity on the Site.

Your email address is publicly displayed and connected to your PupWorld, LLC activity.

Other people may see your date joined, feedback, ratings, profile information, pets listed for sale or for adoption, profile pages, sold listings, and personal reference comments.

PupWorld, LLC automatically receives and records some information from your browser when you visit the site, such as your IP address, cookies and data about which pages you visit on the site through the use of log files provided by our third-party tracking-utility partners. This information helps us analyze and understand how the site works for members and visitors, and provide a more personalized experience for members and visitors.

Some members or visitors may connect to or register a PupWorld, LLC account using an external third-party application, such as Facebook, Google, or Twitter. PupWorld, LLC may receive some data from those connected third-party applications.

Connecting your PupWorld, LLC account to third-party applications or services is optional, and when you connect your account to an external app, you will be given the opportunity to grant permission. PupWorld, LLC may receive or collect information (for example: email address) about a person who is not yet a registered PupWorld, LLC member (a “non-member”) in connection with certain PupWorld, LLC features, including but not limited to: a non-member subscribing to an PupWorld, LLC newsletter, a member inviting a non-member to visit (insert website URL), or

a non-member engaging in a transaction.

Non-member information is used only for the purpose it was originally submitted to PupWorld, LLC. A non-member can contact PupWorld, LLC Support if they do not want PupWorld, LLC to retain their information. PupWorld, LLC uses the information described in this policy to provide and improve our services and products, for billing and payments, for identification and authentication purposes, to contact members or interested parties, and for general research and aggregate reporting. PupWorld, LLC uses cookies to help keep track of items you put into your shopping cart including when you have abandoned your cart and this information is used to determine when to send cart reminder messages via SMS. The above excludes text messaging originator opt-in data and consent; this information will not be shared with any third parties. PupWorld, LLC’s Terms of Use require all account owners to be at least 18 years of age (or have the permission and supervision of a responsible parent or legal guardian), therefore, this policy does not discuss use of our site or services by minors.

Cookies & Tracking Technologies

A cookie is a piece of data stored on the user’s hard drive containing information about the user. Usage of a cookie is in no way linked to any personally identifiable information while on our site. If a user rejects the cookie, they may still use our site. The only drawback to this is that the user will be limited in some areas of our site. Cookies are also used to track promotional discounts on our Site. PupWorld, LLC, may set and access PupWorld, LLC cookies on your computer. PupWorld, LLC lets other companies that show advertisements on some of our pages to set and access their cookies on your computer. Other companies’ use of their cookies is subject to their own privacy policies, not this one. Advertisers or other companies do not have access to PupWorld, LLC cookies.

PupWorld, LLC may partner with third-party services who may use various tracking

technologies, such as browser cookies or Flash cookies, to provide certain services or features. These technologies allow a partner to recognize your computer each time you visit PupWorld, LLC, but do not allow access to personally identifiable information from PupWorld, LLC. PupWorld, LLC does not have access or control over these third-party technologies, and they are not covered by our privacy statement.

Security

The security of your personal information is important to us. Your PupWorld, LLC

account information is protected by a password. It is important that you protect against unauthorized access of your account and information by choosing your password carefully, and keeping your password and computer secure by signing out after using our services. PupWorld, LLC will track the computers, smartphones, and/or any other internet device that is used to access your account including your internet provider and IP Address. If we detect an attempt to sign into your account from a device or internet provider not previously associated with your account then you will be required to input a verification code that will be sent to the email address on file. The code will also be sent as a text message to your mobile phone on file whereas standard message and data rates may apply. PupWorld, LLC encrypts sensitive information (such as credit card number) using secure socket layer technology (SSL). PupWorld, LLC follows generally accepted industry standards to protect the personal information submitted to us, both during transmission and once PupWorld, LLC receives it. No method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
